# 2026-05-08 Personal Provider Lane Execution Board

## Decision Lock

- Public default stays zero-config, generic, consumer-usable, and token-friendly.
- Personal data/runtime requirements must remain opt-in and hot-pluggable.
- Personal profile reuse is allowed only through explicit profile selection or machine-readable discovery, never by silently changing the default lane.
- Same-file execution discipline: update this board in place while implementing.
- No pollution, no debt: narrow edits, focused tests, no new runtime dependency introduced for this slice.

## Hard Constraints

- `provider-status` and `workflow-status` must preserve the generic default path when no profile is selected.
- Agent/machine surfaces must still be able to discover optional personal profile lanes before selection.
- Once a profile is selected, downstream bootstrap/status commands must continue carrying that profile instead of dropping back to generic commands.
- Human-facing unselected output should stay quiet; do not spam personal hints into default human summaries.

## Scope For This Slice

- Close the profile discoverability gap in low-token machine-readable provider/workflow surfaces.
- Close the command propagation gap where bootstrap output dropped selected profiles on the next command hop.
- Rewrite this file into an executable board that reflects verified repo state instead of free-form suggestion text.

